* {{ill|Mizuhanome|ja|ミヅハノメ|lt=Yatsunahome deity|lt_ja=弥津波能売神|12=draft|12=draft}} (Mizuhanome-no-Kami)
* {{ill|Ukemochi|ja|保食神|12=draft|12=draft}} (Ukemochi-no-Kami)
* {{ill|Izanagi|ja|伊邪那岐神|lt=Izanagi-no-Kami|lt_ja=伊邪那岐神|12=draft|12=draft}} (Izanagi-no-Kami)
* {{ill|Izanami|ja|伊邪那美神|lt=Izanami-no-Kami|lt_ja=伊邪那美神|12=draft|12=draft}} (Izanami-no-Kami)

== History ==
* {{ill|1859|ja|1859th year|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft}} 6), established.
* {{ill|1900|ja|1900th year|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft}} 33), upon a petition by the residents, the Ukemochi from the neglected {{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社|12=draft|12=draft}} was enshrined alongside.
* {{ill|1919|ja|1919th year|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Taishō|ja|大正|12=draft|12=draft}} 8), driven by the sentiments of natives from Shiga Prefecture, the shrine building was reconstructed and the two deities known as Nakuin Nison ({{ill|Izanagi|ja|伊邪那岐神|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Izanami|ja|伊邪那美神|12=draft|12=draft}}) from {{ill|Taga Shrine|ja|多賀神社|12=draft|12=draft}} were additionally enshrined.
* {{ill|1923|ja|1923rd year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Taishō 12), it was elevated to a village shrine and designated as a {{ill|Shinsen Heihaku-ryō Kyōshinjinja|ja|神饌幣*

{{Myōken Faith|12=draft|12=draft}}

