'''Suitengu''' (水天宮) is a Shinto shrine located in {{ill|Hokkaido|ja|北海道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hokkaido|qq=}} {{ill|Otaru City|ja|小樽市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otaru City|qq=}}. Its former status was that of a {{ill|Local Shrine|ja|郷社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Local Shrine|qq=}}.

It is sited at a location offering a panoramic view of {{ill|Otaru Port|ja|小樽港|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otaru Port|qq=}}, and is renowned as one of the famous spots for {{ill|Sakura|ja|サクラ|lt=Cherry Blossoms|lt_ja=桜|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakura|qq=}} in Otaru City. The steep stairs and slopes descending toward the seaside area of {{ill|Sakaimachi|ja|堺町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakaimachi|qq=}} are known as Gaijin-zaka<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=https://www.city.otaru.lg.jp/simin/koho/sakamati/1402.html |title=コッフさんと外人坂 前編 |work=おたる坂まち散歩 |publisher={{ill|Otaru City|ja|小樽市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otaru City|qq=}} |accessdate=2016-05-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=https://www.city.otaru.lg.jp/simin/koho/sakamati/1403.html |title=コッフさんと外人坂 後編 |work=おたる坂まち散歩 |publisher=小樽市 |accessdate=2016-05-24}}</ref>. A straight road connects the shrine to {{ill|Otaru Park|ja|小樽公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otaru Park|qq=}}, located on the hillside, thereby integrating the surrounding landscape<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://www.jila-hokkaido.com/gyouji_/kitanozouensisan/kitanozoen_all/4_otaru/Isan-4(Otaru).pdf |title=小樽公園 |format=PDF |publisher={{ill|Japan Landscape Architecture Society|ja|日本造園学会|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japan Landscape Architecture Society|qq=}} Hokkaido Branch |accessdate=2016-05-12}}</ref>. Within the precincts, there stand monuments such as the {{ill|Ishikawa Takuboku|ja|石川啄木|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ishikawa Takuboku|qq=}} poetry monument, the Mitsuya Yōson (みつやようそん) haiku monument, and the {{ill|Kawasomura Bun'ichirō|ja|河邨文一郎|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawasomura Bun'ichirō|qq=}} poetry monument<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://otaru-journal.com/2005/10/post-837.php |title=水天宮の啄木歌碑を移設！新たな装いでお目見え！ |date=2005-10-15 |work={{ill|Otaru Journal|ja|小樽ジャーナル|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otaru Journal|qq=}} |publisher=小樽ジャーナル社 |accessdate=2016-05-24}}</ref>.

== Enshrined Deities ==
The shrines sharing the same name as the Suitengu of {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuoka Prefecture|qq=}} {{ill|Kurume City|ja|久留米市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurume City|qq=}}, designated as the head shrine, enshrine figures including {{ill|Antoku Emperor|ja|安徳天皇|1=Emperor Antoku|2=ja|3=安徳天皇|4=de|5=Antoku|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Antoku Emperor|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Antoku|qq=}}, whereas the deities enshrined here are different and do not belong to that lineage{{Sfn|小野|1999|p=103}}.
